This paper deals with incremental learning and concept drift, which are topics related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. The proposed method, DTEL, involves ensemble learning, which is a common technique in machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves transfer learning, which is a subfield of machine learning, and diversity, which is a concept related to data structures and algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also mentions using the proposed method on image data, which suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision) could be a relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper involves neural networks, which is a subfield of machine learning, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category.
